# Custom Agents

Each agent is a folder in `agents/<name>/` with:
- `agent.json` тАФ config (model, tools, caps, memory, requireApproval)
- `SOUL.md` тАФ core identity, role, and primary instructions (always loaded)
- `skills/` тАФ agent-specific skills (auto-discovered, loaded on demand)
- `BRAIN.db` тАФ persistent memory (created on first deploy, managed by runtime)

Shared skills: `agents/shared-skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`

## agent.json

```json
{
  "name": "invoice-analyzer",
  "model": "claude-sonnet",
  "tools": ["query", "search", "notify"],
  "memory": true,
  "caps": { "maxTurns": 30, "maxCredits": 200, "maxDuration": 300 },
  "requireApproval": ["notify"]
}
```

Model can be a fixed string or dynamic routing:
```json
{ "model": { "fast": "claude-haiku", "balanced": "claude-sonnet", "powerful": "claude-opus" } }
```

## Invoke from workflow

```typescript
const result = await ctx.agent("invoice-analyzer", {
  goal: "Analyze overdue invoices and notify the team",
  context: { threshold: 30 },
  caps: { maxTurns: 10 },
});
// result: { response, output?, usage: { credits, turns, duration }, capped?, cappedReason? }
```

## Tool grants

- `query` тАФ read-only SQL against workspace databases
- `search` тАФ semantic similarity search against synced data
- `ask` тАФ natural language Q&A against databases (search + AI synthesis)
- `notify` тАФ send email (`send_email`) and SMS (`send_sms`)
- `http` тАФ fetch external APIs (`http_request`)
- `workspace` тАФ read/write workspace files
- `ai` тАФ sub-AI calls for classify/extract/summarize (credits count against caps)
- `trigger_workflow` тАФ trigger other workflows (requires `workflows` allowlist in agent.json)
- `custom:<name>` тАФ custom tools defined in SOUL.md

## Brain memory

When memory is configured, the agent gets 4 tools automatically:
- `remember(content, entity?)` тАФ store facts, upsert entities
- `recall(query)` тАФ search memory for entities, facts, struggles
- `log_outcome(action, result, effective?)` тАФ track action effectiveness
- `flag_struggle(category, description)` тАФ signal knowledge gaps or edge cases

Auto-detected struggles (no agent action needed): cap hits, approval rejections, fallback responses.

Session-start digest: entity summaries, recent facts, unresolved struggles, effectiveness stats.

Admin reviews brain via `mug brain <agent-name> struggles`.

## Approval flow

When `requireApproval` lists tool names, agent pauses before calling them. Result includes `status: "pending_approval"` and `pendingApproval: { tool, args }`. Resume by re-invoking with the same `sessionKey`.

## Cap enforcement

When caps are hit, the agent is forced to call `deliver_output` with partial results. `result.capped` is `true` and `result.cappedReason` explains why.
